description:
&lt;p&gt;Nuffield Health is Britain’s largest not-for-profit healthcare organisation. Join us as a Senior Operating Department Practitioner - Anaesthetics in our North Staffordshire Hospital and play your part in building a healthier nation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to work for an award-winning healthcare charity?  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nuffield Health North Staffs Hospital &lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuffield Health is the largest non-profit healthcare organisation in UK. It operates 31 hospitals and 112 gyms, employing over 11,000 people. In Glasgow, Nuffield Health has a Hospital and five Health and Wellbeing centers.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our team at North Staffs Hospital, located in the heart of Stoke. The Nuffield Health North Staffordshire Hospital was opened in 1978 with funds raised by the local community. The hospital is now a modern, purpose-built and well-equipped private healthcare facility with 36 en suite bedrooms. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;There are two operating theatres and one minor/endoscopy suite, a busy outpatient department and physiotherapy, pathology and diagnostic imaging. It has an excellent reputation for clinical care, expertise and efficient friendly staff. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As our Senior Theatre Practitioner - Anaesthetics you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work closely with the Senior Theatre Practitioner - Recovery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work closely with Theatre Manager and Clinical Leaders to ensure comprehensive governance and training is maintained&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Demonstrate Nuffield behaviours framework and inspire colleagues to do the same&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure the patient perioperative journey is a positive one, with clinical safety being at the core of everything we do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The person&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To succeed as a Senior Theatre Practitioner - Anaesthetics you will need:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent clinical skills with the drive to ensure you remain current in your knowledge and ensure best practice is applied.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally a minimum of 4 years’ experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Relevant NMC/HCPC qualification&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want you to be the best you can be. We promise that we will support you with training opportunities, career development options and our unique health &amp; wellbeing focused benefits package. This includes free membership across all of our Fitness &amp; Wellbeing clubs, along with free private healthcare. Not only this, but we also offer a range of lifestyle and financial wellbeing benefits.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Be your best and join us in building a healthier nation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary - Up to £33,500 per annum (dependant on experience)&lt;br /&gt;Closing date - 16/11/2020&lt;br /&gt;Location - Newcastle Under Lyme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type - Permanent&lt;br /&gt;Weekly Hours - 37.5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
